  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strategic Investment for Business Resilience in Shrimps Sector FY1516</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Cooperative will be more resilience to market and business environment. They can keep and increase their market share on Shrimps market and positioning new products presentations. The strategic revolving funds will be used in emergency case when climate extreme events occurs in order to keep the market share and restoring the livelihoods of poor women and men.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will establish a strategic fund on the Cooperative to buy/pay raw materials from small shrimps producers and stakeholders, this fund also will be used by the Cooperative to strength and increase the action on Climate Resilience and Inclusive market development focus on supply chain related to El Zompopero Cooperative.The cooperative can not use this resource for another purpose which was not requested unless Christian Aid approves other activities in writing.The strategic revolving fund will be managed by the Zompopero cooperative for commercial activities related to the gathering center. In the first phase (6 years) the cooperatives will exclusive use of the fund to buy raw material from small producers and stakeholders from 7 rural poor communities and several local shrimps cooperatives.</narrative>
  </description>
